<div class="settings-section-heading">
  <span class="settings-section-icon"><i class="fa fa-link"></i></span>
  <div>
    <h2>Custom domain</h2>
    <p>Connect a domain you own and keep your Neocities site behind a memorable address.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<% if current_site.custom_domain_available? %>
  <div class="settings-domain-intro">
    <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
    <p>You will make these changes at your domain registrar. The examples use <strong>yourdomain.com</strong>; replace it with your own domain. <a href="/img/namecheap-dns-example.png">View a DNS example</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="settings-step-list">
    <section class="settings-step">
      <span>1</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Point the root domain to Neocities</h3>
        <p>Add this required A record. Your registrar may show the root domain as <strong>@</strong>.</p>
        <div class="settings-dns-record"><span>A</span><code>198.51.233.1</code><small>Required</small></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="settings-step">
      <span>2</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Add IPv6 and www support</h3>
        <p>These records are optional, but recommended for broader access and familiar www links.</p>
        <div class="settings-dns-record"><span>AAAA</span><code>2620:2:6000::bad:dab:cafe</code><small>Recommended</small></div>
        <div class="settings-dns-record"><span>CNAME</span><code>www → <span>yourdomain.com</span></code><small>Recommended</small></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="settings-step">
      <span>3</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Remove redirects and allow DNS to update</h3>
        <p>Delete any URL Redirect records, then wait about five minutes. Some providers may take longer to publish changes.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="settings-connect-card">
    <div>
      <span class="settings-kicker">Final step</span>
      <h3>Connect your domain</h3>
      <p>Enter only the root domain—no protocol, path, or www. SSL will be created automatically.</p>
    </div>
    <form method="POST" action="/settings/<%= @site.username %>/custom_domain" class="settings-form">
      <%== csrf_token_input_html %>
      <label for="custom_domain">Domain</label>
      <div class="settings-input-action">
        <input id="custom_domain" class="input-Area" name="domain" type="text" placeholder="yourdomain.com" value="<%= @site.domain %>" autocapitalize="off" autocorrect="off" spellcheck="false">
        <input class="btn-Action" type="submit" value="Update Domain">
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <div class="settings-upgrade-card">
    <span class="settings-upgrade-icon"><i class="fa fa-heart"></i></span>
    <div>
      <span class="settings-kicker">Supporter feature</span>
      <h3>Use your own domain</h3>
      <p>Custom domains are included with Neocities Supporter, along with more storage and multiple sites.</p>
      <a class="btn-Action" href="/supporter">Explore Supporter</a>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>
